    <summary>Remote Desktop Software</summary>
    <description>Connect to a computer remotely, be it from the other end of the office or halfway around the world.
AnyDesk ensures secure and reliable remote desktop connections for IT professionals and on-the-go individuals alike.

**This is a virtual package.** It installs [anydesk.install](https://chocolatey.org/packages/anydesk.install).

#### Package Parameters
The following package parameters can be set:

 * `/PATH:installdirectory` - Install the package to a custom directory
 * `/NOAUTOSTART` - Do not start AnyDesk at bootup
 * `/NOSTARTMENU` - Do not create a Start Menu shortcut
 * `/DESKTOPICON` - Create a desktop shortcut
 * `/UPDATETYPE:type` - Set update mode to `manually`, `disabled`, or `auto` (defaults to disabled)

To pass parameters, use `--params "''"` (e.g. `choco install anydesk.install [other options] --params="'/PATH:C:\Tools\AnyDesk /DESKTOPICON'"`).
To have choco remember parameters on upgrade, be sure to set `choco feature enable -n=useRememberedArgumentsForUpgrades`.</description>
    <releaseNotes>http://download.anydesk.com/changelog.txt</releaseNotes>
    <dependencies>
